Typr OSS

This project descends from work originally published by Fastrepl in the Anarlog / Hyprnote codebase:

  https://github.com/fastrepl/anarlog

The project is distributed under the GNU General Public License v3.0. See LICENSE.

Typr-specific changes include OSS sanitization, BYOK cloud provider configuration, local-first defaults, documentation, and removal of private commercial infrastructure from the public source tree.

Bundled runtime and test assets are listed in docs/bundled-assets.md.

Selected bundled binary assets:

- ONNX Runtime for Windows, MIT License, Microsoft Corporation:
  https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime
- DTLN denoise models, MIT License, Nils L. Westhausen:
  https://github.com/breizhn/DTLN
- DTLN-aec acoustic echo cancellation models, MIT License, Nils L. Westhausen:
  https://github.com/breizhn/DTLN-aec
- pyannote segmentation model / ONNX conversion, MIT License:
  https://huggingface.co/pyannote/segmentation
  https://huggingface.co/onnx-community/pyannote-segmentation-3.0
- WeSpeaker VoxCeleb CAM++ speaker embedding model, Apache License 2.0:
  https://huggingface.co/Wespeaker/wespeaker-voxceleb-campplus
